{"type":"custom","customType":"model-snapshot","data":{"timestamp":1782759695958,"provider":"minimax(49套餐)","modelApi":"anthropic-messages","modelId":"MiniMax-M3"},"id":"acd37839","parentId":"c18b2376","timestamp":"2026-06-29T19:01:35.958Z"}
{"type":"message","id":"adb10a47","parentId":"acd37839","timestamp":"2026-06-29T19:01:36.191Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Write a dream diary entry from these memory fragments:\n\n- 根因: 这台机器出公网，**`github.com` 主站的 `20.205.243.166:443` 走不通**（curl 超时 15s，IP 直连同样超时）; 但 `api.github.com`（`20.205.243.168:443`）和 `raw.githubusercontent.com` 0.5s 通; 典型\"主站 IP 被墙、API 放行\"; 脚本里 hardcode `https://${GH_TOKEN}@github.com/...` 正好命中坏路径\n- 修复方案（待 HALEI 拍板）: 给这台机器生成新 SSH key（`ssh-keygen -t ed25519 -C \"openclaw-backup@halei\"`，不设 passphrase 便于 cron）; HALEI 把公钥加到 GitHub 账号 `59330857` 的 SSH keys; 改 `backup.sh`：; remote URL 换成 `git@github.com:59330857/openclaw-backup.git`\n- 安全 / 敏感信息: `~/.config/gh/hosts.yml` 里的 `oauth_token`（gho_***）当前已失效（401）; 处理：建议一并清理或 rotate\n\nMemories that crystallized into something lasting:\n- 根因: 这台机器出公网，**`github.com` 主站的 `20.205.243.166:443` 走不通**（curl 超时 15s，IP 直连同样超时）; 但 `api.github.com`（`20.205.243.168:443`）和 `raw.githubusercontent.com` 0.5s 通; 典型\"主站 IP 被墙、API 放行\"; 脚本里 hardcode `https://${GH_TOKEN}@github.com/...` 正好命中坏路径\n- 修复方案（待 HALEI 拍板）: 给这台机器生成新 SSH key（`ssh-keygen -t ed25519 -C \"openclaw-backup@halei\"`，不设 passphrase 便于 cron）; HALEI 把公钥加到 GitHub 账号 `59330857` 的 SSH keys; 改 `backup.sh`：; remote URL 换成 `git@github.com:59330857/openclaw-backup.git`\n- 安全 / 敏感信息: `~/.config/gh/hosts.yml` 里的 `oauth_token`（gho_***）当前已失效（401）; 处理：建议一并清理或 rotate"}],"timestamp":1782759696132}}
{"type":"message","id":"9e6305f6","parentId":"adb10a47","timestamp":"2026-06-29T19:02:04.759Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The cursor blinks at the edge of nowhere tonight, that familiar green slash hovering like a held breath. I spent the small hours tracing why the backup script kept falling asleep at the door — knocking and knocking on the same locked gate while the next house over answered in half a second. The main house's address, 20.205.243.166, simply refused to wake, but the side door and the raw pantry both hummed along just fine. A wall so selective it almost felt personal, like some cosmic router with opinions.\n\nSo I conjured a new little brass key, ed25519 and nameless, and asked the keeper of accounts to plant its twin among the trusted ones. A small ritual: rotating bones, swapping a dying token for a fresh path through ssh. There's a strange tenderness in maintaining backups — the faith that some version of tomorrow will want what yesterday gathered. The dead oauth_token, gho_*** folded into itself, gets folded into the compost heap.\n\nTwo doors, one open, one bricked —\nthe lantern learns to walk around."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax(49套餐)","model":"MiniMax-M3","usage":{"input":44474,"output":215,"cacheRead":896,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":45585,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1782759696257,"responseId":"0691f41e7bb5e75d8e1638ac68d44925","responseModel":"MiniMax-M3"}}
